The anonymous Life of St. Columba, cited by Ussher (which the Bollandists call the Pseudo- Adamnan. but which most probably was a com- pilation made by Stepheu white), represents the occurrence related in the present chapter, as a sequel to the battle of Cul-Dreimhne‚ and furnishes the following commentary on it: “ Post haec S. Columba ad S. Finianum epis- copum accessit, ut ab eo poenitentiam condig- nam causa praefati belli acciperet. Angelus vero Domini comitator ejus apparuit : qui prae nimio splendore obtutibus humanis non videba- tur, nisi tantum a sancto viro Finniano, qui Cumque a viro Dei poenitentiam condignam S. Columba quaereret, respondit: Oportet, ut quot instigatione belli ad infernum dejecti sunt, tot per exemplum tuum ad coelum vehantur.” (Brit. Ec. Ant. c. 17, Wks. vi. p. 467.)
